questions.solution:
- **`break`**: Exits the enclosing loop (or switch) immediately. Use when you've found what you're looking for and don't need to continue iterating.
  ```java
  for (int i = 0; i < 10; i++) {
      if (i == 5) break; // stops at 5
  }
  ```

- **`continue`**: Skips the rest of the current iteration and moves to the next. Use to skip certain elements.
  ```java
  for (int i = 0; i < 10; i++) {
      if (i % 2 == 0) continue; // skip even numbers
      System.out.println(i);
  }
  ```

- **`return`**: Exits the entire method, returning a value (or void). Use when the loop is inside a helper method and you want to return early.
  ```java
  boolean contains(int[] arr, int target) {
      for (int n : arr) {
          if (n == target) return true;
      }
      return false;
  }
  ```

questions.question:
A junior developer wrote this FizzBuzz loop:
```java
for (int i = 1; i <= 20; i++) {
    if (i % 3 == 0)
        System.out.println("Fizz");
    if (i % 5 == 0)
        System.out.println("Buzz");
    if (i % 3 != 0 && i % 5 != 0)
        System.out.println(i);
}
```
For i=15, what does this print? What is wrong with the code and how would you fix it using `else if`?

questions.solution:
**Problem:** For i=15, the code prints:
```
Fizz
Buzz
```
on two separate lines. The correct output should be `FizzBuzz` on one line.

**Fixed version:**
```java
for (int i = 1; i <= 20; i++) {
    if (i % 15 == 0) {         // check both first
        System.out.println("FizzBuzz");
    } else if (i % 3 == 0) {
        System.out.println("Fizz");
    } else if (i % 5 == 0) {
        System.out.println("Buzz");
    } else {
        System.out.println(i);
    }
}
```
The key fix: check `i % 15 == 0` (divisible by both 3 and 5) **before** the individual checks, and use `else if` so only one branch executes.

public class PrimeFinder {
    static boolean isPrime(int n) {
        if (n <= 1) return false;
        for (int i = 2; i <= Math.sqrt(n); i++) {
            if (n % i == 0) return false;
        }
        return true;
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        System.out.print("Primes 1-50: ");
        for (int i = 1; i <= 50; i++) {
            if (isPrime(i)) System.out.print(i + " ");
        }
        System.out.println();
    }
}

