**Problem:** `String result += line` in a loop creates a **new String object every iteration**. After 10,000 iterations, you've created ~10,000 temporary strings and put enormous pressure on the garbage collector. Time complexity is O(n²) because each concatenation copies all previous content.

**Correct solution using StringBuilder:**
```java
StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();
for (String line : lines) {
    sb.append(line);
    sb.append("\n");
}
String result = sb.toString();
```

`StringBuilder` maintains a **mutable character buffer** — `append()` adds to the existing buffer without creating new objects. Time complexity is O(n). For a 10,000-line report, this can be **100x+ faster**.

public class PalindromeChecker {
    static boolean isPalindrome(String s) {
        String cleaned = s.replaceAll("\\s+", "").toLowerCase();
        int left = 0, right = cleaned.length() - 1;
        while (left < right) {
            if (cleaned.charAt(left) != cleaned.charAt(right)) return false;
            left++;
            right--;
        }
        return true;
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        System.out.println(isPalindrome("racecar"));                    // true
        System.out.println(isPalindrome("A man a plan a canal Panama")); // true
        System.out.println(isPalindrome("hello"));                       // false
    }
}

